Gregory N. (Greg) Roberts 

		
		President and CEO, 

	
		 Spectrum Group International, Inc. 	

 
Last Updated: 07/16/2012 



Executive Summary
Roberts is President and Chief Executive Officer of Spectrum Group International (formerly known as Escala), an Irvine, California-based collectibles company that specializes in coins, bullion, stamps and wine. Roberts took the reins of the company in March 2008, eight years after he became a Director. He also serves as President of Sp 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Roberts is married, with children.
His annual base salary, as of fiscal year 2011, was $525,000. 
Current Focus
Corporate Snapshot: Spectrum Group International is the third-largest collectibles firm in the world, behind Christies and Sotheby's. The company is a trader of precious metal products such as gold, silver, platinum, 
Key Challenges

Wine Fraud Charges: Spectrum Group International in March 2012 issued an official statement in which Roberts sought to distance itself from a high-profile wine dealer who allegedly tried to sell counterfeit wine at one  
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1962 in Pasadena, California.
After graduating from high school in 1980, Roberts joined Quality Coin Exchange, a father-son wholesale partnership operated by Nick Buzolich Sr. and Nick Buzolich Jr. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Professional Numismatists Guild (PNG)
Member, American Numismatic Association (ANA) 
 





